<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1071880-to-those-who-disagree-with-crichton-on">To those who disagree with Crichton on this issue, why do you think he came to the conclusions he did and what special interest would propel him to write this book?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1071880'><a id="like_count_community_question_1071880" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1071880?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15860.State_of_Fear">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1071880-to-those-who-disagree-with-crichton-on">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1071880-to-those-who-disagree-with-crichton-on">See all 5 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/53444598-infinity-s-bookshelf"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1559572730i/53444598._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/53444598-infinity-s-bookshelf">Infinity&#39;s  Bookshelf</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">He came to the conclusions he did because the world hadn&apos;t really seen the effects yet. I don&apos;t think he consciously attempted to misappropriate data <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">He came to the conclusions he did because the world hadn't really seen the effects yet. I don't think he consciously attempted to misappropriate data to form this book. He was simply speaking from the playbook that the climate change deniers spoke from. Now, while Texas has the worst winter storm in decades, wildfires destroy land on three continents and islands are being swallowed by the ocean, we have to acknowledge that even if humans aren't causing this, we are going to have to survive it somehow. Back in 2003, they had no idea the scale of the problem. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
